        <p>
            Now that we have the form, we can add buttons to submit and reset it.
            <br/><br/>
            Additionally, we can style the buttons with custom CSS.
            <br/><br/>
            Finally, note that we can display an Alert from the Controller  when the form is submitted.
        </p>
        <br>
        <h4>Controller</h4>
        <pre><code>[HttpGet]
public IActionResult Buttons() => View(new UserProfile());

[HttpPost]
public IActionResult Buttons(UserProfile formData)
{
   return View(formData)
       .Success($"Submitted {formData.First} {formData.Last}.");
}</code></pre>
        
    </div>
</div>

@section Scripts {
    @{await Html.RenderPartialAsync("_ValidationScriptsPartial");}
}